WEBVTT

00:03.406 --> 00:04.945
How you feeling, Erica?

00:04.970 --> 00:06.781
One blackout away from being able

00:06.806 --> 00:08.119
to have little ones, I hope.

00:08.144 --> 00:09.563
Absolutely.

00:09.564 --> 00:11.183
And I told your husband the same thing.

00:11.184 --> 00:13.603
He's in the waiting room
with your mom, dad.

00:13.604 --> 00:16.062
<i>You are going to
knock me out, right?</i>

00:16.064 --> 00:17.893
The doctor didn't say.

00:17.894 --> 00:19.813
Dr. Robeson's not one to chat.

00:19.814 --> 00:23.273
Trust me, you'll miss the whole thing.

00:23.274 --> 00:24.273
Julio, some help?

00:24.274 --> 00:24.879
Okay.

00:24.880 --> 00:25.483
On three.

00:25.484 --> 00:27.644
One, two, three.

00:29.394 --> 00:30.603
There we go. Let's bring in Atticus.

00:30.604 --> 00:32.643
Is that the robot arm?

00:32.644 --> 00:34.183
It's the Atticus
Surgical System.

00:34.184 --> 00:35.273
It's the best tool for the job.

00:35.274 --> 00:36.274
Where's my music?

00:36.275 --> 00:37.273
Coming, Doctor.

00:37.274 --> 00:39.813
Okay, Erica Povery, myomectomy.

00:39.814 --> 00:41.313
Hi, Dr. Robeson.

00:41.314 --> 00:42.563
Hi, Ms. Povery.

00:42.564 --> 00:44.143
Here's your music, Doctor.

00:44.144 --> 00:46.143
Give me 100 mikes of fentanyl,
then the propofol.

00:46.144 --> 00:48.233
All right, you're gonna feel
a chill come over you.

00:48.234 --> 00:49.353
Count down from ten.

00:49.354 --> 00:51.249
Ten, nine... Good.

00:51.250 --> 00:53.143
Ten, nine, eight...

00:53.144 --> 00:55.023
seven...

00:55.024 --> 00:57.603
There's more fibroids in
the uterus than we thought.

00:59.354 --> 01:00.683
Heavy bleeding from that insertion.

01:00.684 --> 01:03.024
- I see it.
- Blood pressure's dropping fast.

01:03.027 --> 01:04.684
- We've gotta stop this bleeding.
- I know.

01:04.687 --> 01:06.313
She's bleeding out. This isn't working.

01:07.432 --> 01:09.353
Dr. Robeson, what do you want me to do?

01:14.414 --> 01:16.118
Dr. Terrence Robeson.

01:16.143 --> 01:17.823
First in his class at Harvard Med.

01:17.824 --> 01:19.743
Now one of the top gynecological surgeons

01:19.744 --> 01:21.033
in the world.

01:21.034 --> 01:24.323
Terry and I went to college together.

01:24.324 --> 01:25.453
- Terry...
- Ooh.

01:25.454 --> 01:27.123
Wait, he looks like that,

01:27.124 --> 01:29.164
<i>- and he's a surgeon?
- Doesn't seem right, does it?</i>

01:29.167 --> 01:30.534
- What'd he do?
- Saved a woman's life,

01:30.537 --> 01:32.493
And now she's suing him for it.

01:32.494 --> 01:35.493
Erica Povery.

01:35.494 --> 01:37.493
She and her husband
wanted to start a family.

01:37.494 --> 01:40.283
But a cluster of fibroids
was preventing pregnancy.

01:40.284 --> 01:42.203
Terry was brought in to remove them.

01:42.204 --> 01:44.953
Unfortunately, there were a larger number

01:44.954 --> 01:46.658
of fibroids than expected.

01:46.683 --> 01:48.746
Now, heavy bleeding is not uncommon,

01:48.771 --> 01:50.743
but in Erica's case,
the bleeding wouldn't stop.

01:50.744 --> 01:51.993
The only way to keep her alive

01:51.994 --> 01:53.323
was to remove her uterus

01:53.324 --> 01:55.573
and perform an emergency hysterectomy.

01:55.574 --> 01:57.323
So now she can't have kids?

01:57.324 --> 01:59.823
And that's why she had the
surgery in the first place?

01:59.824 --> 02:02.453
Erica is claiming that the
hysterectomy was avoidable,

02:02.454 --> 02:04.073
and she's suing for malpractice.

02:04.074 --> 02:05.663
Well, to prove malpractice,
she has to show

02:05.664 --> 02:08.622
that Robeson violated a
reasonable standard of care.

02:08.624 --> 02:11.913
That means a significant
violation of skill,

02:11.914 --> 02:13.823
diligence, or judgment.

02:13.824 --> 02:14.869
Not easy to do.

02:14.870 --> 02:15.913
Maybe not.

02:15.914 --> 02:17.533
But there are people
with skill, diligence,

02:17.534 --> 02:20.123
and judgment lining up
to testify against him.

02:20.124 --> 02:23.073
My guess is the they're
gonna focus on one aspect.

02:23.074 --> 02:25.556
That he rushed the decision
to perform the hysterectomy.

02:25.581 --> 02:26.533
Judgment.

02:26.534 --> 02:28.323
They're gonna say that he could have used

02:28.324 --> 02:30.073
less-drastic measures
to stop the bleeding.

02:30.074 --> 02:32.493
And there's diligence.

02:32.494 --> 02:35.865
Okay, listen, I know that it sounds bad,

02:35.890 --> 02:37.703
but I've known Terry for 16 years.

02:37.704 --> 02:39.951
If there was another way,
he would have found it.

02:39.976 --> 02:41.420
What about the hospital?

02:41.445 --> 02:42.913
They offered a settlement.

02:42.914 --> 02:44.533
But Terry refused.

02:44.534 --> 02:46.057
It would have meant admitting
that he made a mistake,

02:46.081 --> 02:48.664
- and he insisted he didn't make one.
- So if he loses,

02:48.667 --> 02:50.835
He'll be held liable for damages,

02:50.860 --> 02:52.309
which could be millions.

02:52.310 --> 02:54.149
And he may never practice again.

02:54.150 --> 02:58.269
For someone like Terry...
Brilliant, a pioneer...

02:58.270 --> 02:59.689
That's all he has.

02:59.690 --> 03:01.689
I'm assuming that the good doctor has

03:01.690 --> 03:03.099
an equally accomplished lawyer?

03:03.100 --> 03:05.479
Actually, no. He's had some

03:05.480 --> 03:08.189
disagreements with his lawyers.

03:08.190 --> 03:10.229
<i>Lawyers? Plural?</i>

03:10.230 --> 03:12.309
They sent over some pre-trial files

03:12.310 --> 03:14.269
and motions.

03:14.270 --> 03:16.399
I could pull 'em up.

03:16.400 --> 03:18.859
All right.

03:18.860 --> 03:20.649
Let's see what we're up against.

03:20.650 --> 03:23.608
At this time, we,
the plaintiffs would like to call

03:23.633 --> 03:25.820
Dr. Terrence Robeson to the stand.

03:25.845 --> 03:28.359
Benny's a little too excited
to play Erica's attorney.

03:28.360 --> 03:30.939
Residual nostalgia from
his prosecutor days.

03:30.940 --> 03:33.189
But don't worry, it's what we
need to find the weaknesses

03:33.190 --> 03:34.649
in your old boyfriend's case.

03:34.650 --> 03:37.359
Terry. Sharp intake of breath

03:37.360 --> 03:39.599
tells me it was no more than a year.

03:39.600 --> 03:41.189
You're trying to be relaxed, which means

03:41.190 --> 03:42.859
it was a long time ago, but...

03:42.860 --> 03:45.820
that little pulsing vein is the giveaway.

03:45.845 --> 03:47.369
He still has a place in your heart.

03:47.394 --> 03:50.859
It is hard not to feel
continually judged by you.

03:50.860 --> 03:53.599
Well... not judged. Observed.

03:53.600 --> 03:55.269
And you shouldn't be insulted, because

03:55.270 --> 03:56.729
I can't help it.

03:56.730 --> 03:58.559
We were together almost a year,
after college.

03:58.560 --> 04:00.099
Still close friends.

04:00.100 --> 04:01.559
Why didn't you tell me about him?

04:01.560 --> 04:03.229
Well, I...

04:03.230 --> 04:04.649
Terry's...

04:04.650 --> 04:06.769
an acquired taste.

04:06.770 --> 04:09.599
Well, let's see what we can
acquire from Terry's stand-in.

04:09.600 --> 04:11.269
Dr. Robeson, as simply

04:11.270 --> 04:13.649
as you can, please walk
us through the surgery.

04:13.650 --> 04:17.228
Certainly. We began with anesthesia,

04:17.230 --> 04:18.978
a mix of fentanyl and Marcaine.

04:18.980 --> 04:21.100
- Then once the patient had...
- Wrong.

04:21.103 --> 04:23.649
Wh... Are you insane?

04:23.650 --> 04:25.189
It's fentanyl then propofol.

04:25.190 --> 04:27.655
Marcaine would have the
inconvenient effect

04:27.680 --> 04:29.229
of giving her seizures

04:29.230 --> 04:30.438
and putting her in a coma.

04:30.463 --> 04:32.729
Terry, you were supposed to
call me when you got here.

04:32.730 --> 04:34.399
I... I know, I just wanted

04:34.400 --> 04:36.729
to see the magic happen.

04:36.730 --> 04:38.899
We'll be sawing Marissa in half later.

04:38.900 --> 04:41.399
You should stick around.
I'm Dr. Jason Bull.

04:41.400 --> 04:43.809
You're a psychologist, though, right?

04:43.810 --> 04:45.399
So, not a real doctor.

04:45.400 --> 04:47.599
W... Now, this is
all part of trial science.

04:47.600 --> 04:49.809
This is where we run the
mock trials with experts,

04:49.810 --> 04:51.439
like this MD.

04:51.440 --> 04:53.769
- Yeah.
- And we present various facts

04:53.770 --> 04:57.665
in the case and track
the juror's responses.

04:57.690 --> 05:00.895
And once we hone our
strategy, we bring you in.

05:00.920 --> 05:03.071
Well, based on your so-called expert,

05:03.072 --> 05:04.928
I'd say you need to bring me in now.

05:04.953 --> 05:07.611
We didn't want to waste your time,
given your busy schedule.

05:07.612 --> 05:08.991
But since you're here...

05:08.992 --> 05:11.531
ain't nothing better than the real thing.

05:11.532 --> 05:12.782
Okay.

05:13.980 --> 05:15.019
Get out of there.

05:15.020 --> 05:17.019
Like I said... acquired taste.

05:17.020 --> 05:19.309
Wow.

05:19.310 --> 05:20.649
Dr. Robeson,

05:20.650 --> 05:22.979
you're considered the top surgeon

05:22.980 --> 05:24.479
in your field, is that correct?

05:24.480 --> 05:25.899
And I'd kill to keep it that way.

05:25.900 --> 05:28.059
It's a joke.

05:28.060 --> 05:29.378
Right. Right,

05:29.403 --> 05:31.269
well, let's just talk about
Erica's case, okay?

05:31.270 --> 05:32.519
There's a line of surgeons

05:32.520 --> 05:33.859
who will testify

05:33.860 --> 05:35.729
that you should have waited

05:35.730 --> 05:37.829
to perform a radical hysterectomy.

05:37.854 --> 05:40.059
Yeah, I can get you a line of
idiots to tell you anything.

05:40.060 --> 05:41.939
Especially doctors who
are paid to come to court

05:41.940 --> 05:43.310
- instead of the operating room.
- Are you aware

05:43.313 --> 05:45.059
That you perform fibroid surgery

05:45.060 --> 05:47.099
in half the time as the national average?

05:47.100 --> 05:49.900
- Yes. - So, isn't it possible
that you might have

05:49.903 --> 05:53.019
Rushed through surgery to fit
more in, make more money?

05:53.020 --> 05:55.520
Is it possible you were fired
by the D.A. for incompetence?

06:00.230 --> 06:01.649
I see you did your due diligence.

06:01.650 --> 06:02.730
In the O.R....

06:02.731 --> 06:03.809
Yeah, in the O.R.

06:03.810 --> 06:06.599
I pioneered the use of a
robotic arm called the Atticus,

06:06.600 --> 06:08.519
which allows me to
perform fibroid surgery

06:08.520 --> 06:09.939
in half the time with one thousandth

06:09.940 --> 06:11.439
the number of mistakes.

06:11.440 --> 06:13.269
Their empathy
lines are plummeting.

06:13.270 --> 06:14.979
I'm no surgeon,
but wouldn't you call

06:14.980 --> 06:16.683
- maiming Erica a mistake?
- No,

06:16.708 --> 06:18.977
because she lived. And you're
right, you're no surgeon.

06:19.002 --> 06:21.285
You have no idea what it's
like when every decision,

06:21.310 --> 06:22.689
every incision you make

06:22.690 --> 06:24.301
is the difference between life and death.

06:24.325 --> 06:26.057
It's bloody, it's ugly,

06:26.058 --> 06:28.307
and it's nothing anyone
who went to law school

06:28.308 --> 06:31.347
should be able to second guess.
So let me make this... simple.

06:31.348 --> 06:33.637
The closest thing that
we have to God on Earth

06:33.638 --> 06:35.677
is a surgeon at the top of his game.

06:35.678 --> 06:38.228
So next time...

06:39.678 --> 06:42.228
...you know, maybe laugh at his jokes.

06:43.428 --> 06:46.517
Well, your friend may
have saved Erica's life,

06:46.518 --> 06:49.138
but he just took his own on the stand.

